hands_on_practices.solution:
The mass flow rate at standard conditions is the product of volumetric flow and density:
$$\dot{m}=\dot V\,\rho.$$
1. Convert scfm to SI volumetric flow:
$$\dot V_{\rm SI}
=\dot V_{\rm scfm}\,\frac{k_{ftm}^{3}}{k_{mis}}.$$
2. Density of dry air from the ideal-gas law:
$$\rho
=\frac{P_{std}\,M_{air}}{R_{u}\,T_{std}},\quad
M_{air}=y_{N_2}M_{N_2}+y_{O_2}M_{O_2}.$$
3. Combine to identify $C$:
$$\dot m_{kg/s}
=\dot V_{\rm scfm}
\frac{k_{ftm}^{3}}{k_{mis}}
\frac{P_{std}(y_{N_2}M_{N_2}+y_{O_2}M_{O_2})}{R_{u}T_{std}}
\equiv C\,\dot V_{\rm scfm}.$$
4. Substitute numerical constants:
$$M_{air}
=0.79\times0.028013+0.21\times0.031999
=0.02885006\;{\rm kg/mol},$$
$$\frac{P_{std}}{R_{u}T_{std}}
=\frac{100000}{8.31446\times273.15}
=44.03024768\;{\rm mol/m^3},$$
$$\rho
=44.03024768\times0.02885006
=1.27057698\;{\rm kg/m^3},$$
$$\frac{k_{ftm}^3}{k_{mis}}
=\frac{0.3048^3}{60}
=0.0004719474432\;{\rm m^3/(s\cdot scfm)},$$
$$C
=0.0004719474432\times1.27057698
=5.996106722\times10^{-4}\;\frac{\rm kg}{\rm s\cdot scfm}.$$
